Etymology.
The species epithet, 

zoque

, is an indeclinable word and refers to the Selva Zoque, a region comprised of tropical forest and covering the areas about Uxpanapa (
Veracruz
), Chimalapas (
Oaxaca
) and El Ocote (
Chiapas
). This region includes part of the historical range of Zoque culture, an ethnic group that has inhabited this region since pre-Columbian times.
